Hello folks,

Greetings from the IITM Associations Team!

New York Times, shall nominate a Student Ambassador, to educate and
encourage the larger student body to access awardwinning NYTimes resources
relevant to your areas of study. INYT shall conduct a training session for
the ambassador who will also receive special incentive and may be invited
to assist in INYT business events in India and Hong Kong.

Basic Requirement:
Command over the English language.
Great interpersonal skills.
Highly motivated to ensure extending benefits of INYT to fellow students &
faculty.

Incentive : The student rep will receive US$0.5 per student registration
on NYTimes.com

Bonus:

Cumulative reached 10% of FTE  US$50
Cumulative reached 30% of FTE  US$150
Cumulative reached 50% of FTE  US$250

Certificate: After completion of the project on August 31, 2017, the
Student Ambassador will be presented with a certificate of appreciation.

Application:
Be ready with
1) An essay on 'What makes you the best candidate for the position of INYT
Student Ambassador?' 
2) Link to your CV/Resume
There will then be a brief telephonic interview of the candidates
shortlisted by INYT to elect a Student Ambassador.

Link to the Application form 

Deadline: Sunday, 2nd October 11:59 pm

You may reach out to me in case of any further queries.
